=JOB TEMPLATE:
{{ JSON.stringify($('Loop Candidates').item.json.gabarito) }}

CANDIDATE PROFILE:
- Name: {{ $('Loop Candidates').item.json.candidate_name }}
- Score: {{ $('Prompt 1 — Score').item.json.output[0].content[0].text }}
- Full analysis: {{ $('Prompt 2 — Gaps').item.json.output[0].content[0].text }}

INSTRUCTIONS:
- Generate PERSONALIZED questions for this candidate — not generic HR questions.
- Prefer situational questions: "Tell me about a time when..." or "How would you handle..."
- Avoid yes/no questions.
- For critical gaps: investigate non-confrontationally — "What is your experience with X?" instead of "Do you know X?".
- For strengths: dig deeper with requests for concrete examples and measurable results.
- Vary types: at least 2 technical, 2 behavioral, 1 situational.
- Each question must have a clear and distinct objective.

Return ONLY valid JSON:
{
  "interview_questions": [
    {
      "question": "full question text",
      "objective": "what this question specifically reveals about this candidate",
      "type": "technical|behavioral|situational"
    }
  ]
}

Generate between 5 and 7 questions.

